{
  "texts": [
    "The split-variable strategy greatly facilitates maintaining the divergence-free condition.",
    "In the simulations with nonzero equilibrium background, the ∇ • B = 0 is analytically fulfilled in the initial state and it remains so through the whole simulation since the initial state is not evolved.",
    "Since the code operates in perturbations, it allows keeping the ∇ • B = 0 condition to the zero order.",
    "We also find that our centered numerical scheme allows keeping ∇ • B = 0 to a good degree of precision in the simulations with full variables (zero background).",
    "In order to check the behavior of ∇ • B = 0 we perform a 3D simulation of the Rayleigh-Taylor instability (RTI), where a dense plasma lies on top of a less-dense plasma with typical solar atmosphere parameters for the density and temperature."
  ]
}